' PlantUML example — Implementation layer: domain class model behind the
' Order entity, including behaviour (operations), not just relationships.
'
' Derived from:
'   - canon/elements/02_business/products/PRODUCT-ECOMM-1.yaml
'       type: digital_product; capabilities: [CAPABILITY-V1, CAPABILITY-V2].
'   - canon/elements/02_business/capabilities/CAPABILITY-V1.yaml — "Order Management"
'   - canon/views/state/order-lifecycle.state.md
'       states: Received, Validating, Picking, BackorderHold, Shipped, Closed.
'
' Not a duplicate of canon/views/er/domain-entities.er.md: that Mermaid ER
' diagram shows entity attributes and relationships (data shape). This class
' diagram adds operations/behaviour (validate(), cancel(), ship()) — detail
' an ER diagram does not carry by convention.

!include transitrix-theme.puml
@startuml Order domain — class model

class Customer #e8f2f5 {
  +id: string
  +consentStatus: string
  +placeOrder(): Order
}

class Order #ccd8dc {
  +id: string
  +status: string
  +validate(): bool
  +cancel(): void
  +ship(): void
}

class OrderLine #e8f2f5 {
  +productId: string
  +quantity: int
}

class Product #e8f2f5 {
  +id: string
  +type: string
  +domain: string
}

class Capability #b3c8cf {
  +id: string
  +name: string
}

Customer "1" -- "0..*" Order : places
Order "1" *-- "1..*" OrderLine : contains
OrderLine "0..*" --> "1" Product : references
Product "1" -- "1..*" Capability : realised by

note right of Order
  status values follow
  canon/views/state/order-lifecycle.state.md:
  Received | Validating | Picking |
  BackorderHold | Shipped | Closed
end note

@enduml
